  "prompt": "How do you use Google Account Recovery to reset your password?",
  "response": "To reset your Google account password using Google Account Recovery, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Go to the Google Account Recovery Page**: Open a web browser and go to the Google Account Recovery page by visiting [accounts.google.com/signin/recovery](https://accounts.google.com/signin/recovery).\n\n2. **Enter Your Email or Phone Number**: On the recovery page, you'll be prompted to enter the email address or phone number associated with your Google account. After entering it, click \"Next.\"\n\n3. **Identify Your Account**: Google will try to help you identify your account. If prompted, follow the instructions to enter any information required (like your last remembered password).\n\n4. **Choose the Recovery Option**: Google will offer various recovery options, such as sending a verification code to your backup email or phone number. Select the method you'd like to use and click \u201cNext.\u201d \n\n5. **Receive and Enter the Code**: If you chose to receive a verification code (via SMS or email), check your phone or email inbox for that code. Enter it into the provided field and click \u201cNext.\u201d\n\n6. **Reset Your Password**: Once your identity is verified, you'll be prompted to create a new password. Make sure to choose a strong password that you have not used before.\n\n7. **Secure Your Account**: After resetting your password, you'll be taken to your Google account. It\u2019s a good idea to check your account recovery options and update any outdated information to help secure your account in the future.\n\n8. **Sign in with Your New Password**: Finally, sign in using your new password to ensure everything works correctly.\n\nIf you encounter any issues during the recovery process, follow the on-screen instructions as Google may provide additional assistance or ask for more verification steps based on your account settings.",
